# HOA Project Funding — Marketing Machine Master Plan

> **Purpose**: This document is a complete execution blueprint for Claude Code in VS Code.
> Follow it section by section. Each phase builds on the previous one.
> The goal: build a fully automated marketing machine that drives qualified leads to hoaprojectfunding.com.

---

## Context & Architecture Overview

### What Already Exists
- **hoaprojectfunding.com** — Live site, accepts applications, "3 simple steps" intake, promises 48-72hr preliminary decisions, multi-lender bid model
- **ClawOps Console** — Chat-centric command center for OpenClaw browser automation agents (React 18 + Vite + Express + SQLite). All 6 dev phases complete, currently in Phase 0 security hardening
- **OpenClaw Agent** — Browser automation agent application in development
- **Marketing team** — Being assembled

### What We're Building
A **Marketing Automation Machine** — an integrated system of:
1. **SEO Content Engine** — Trigger-based content that captures high-intent searches
2. **Lead Capture & Qualification Pipeline** — Two-stage intake with pre-qual scoring
3. **CRM & Workflow Automation** — HubSpot Free + n8n/Make for deterministic lead routing
4. **Partner Distribution System** — Outreach tooling for management companies, reserve study firms, contractors
5. **Nurture & Follow-Up System** — Email/SMS sequences with CAN-SPAM/TCPA compliance
6. **Analytics & Feedback Loops** — Every funded project becomes content, every rejection becomes "what to fix" education
7. **OpenClaw Agent Integration** — Browser agents that automate repetitive marketing ops tasks

### Target Market (by the numbers)
- 365,000+ U.S. community associations
- 28.2 million housing units, 75.5 million residents
- 2.5 million volunteer board/committee members
- 60,000-65,000 community association managers
- 9,000-10,000 management companies
- 30-40% of associations are self-managed (highest pain, least support)

### Priority Geographies
1. **California** (~50,700 associations) — SB 326 deadlines, reserve study cadence (Civil Code §5550)
2. **Florida** (~49,800 associations) — SIRS funding, milestone inspections (post-Surfside legislation)
3. **Texas** (~22,300 associations) — Large installed base, growing market

---

## Phase 1: SEO Content Engine (Days 1-7)

### Objective
Build a static site generator or content management system that produces high-quality, trigger-based SEO pages. These pages target the **moments when boards are forced to act** — not generic "HOA loan" queries.

### Architecture Decision
Create a **Next.js-based content hub** (or Astro if pure static is preferred) that:
- Lives at a subdomain or path on hoaprojectfunding.com (e.g., `/resources/`, `/guides/`)
- Generates SEO-optimized pages from structured content templates
- Includes schema markup (FAQ, HowTo, Article) for rich snippets
- Has proper internal linking to main site's intake form

### Content Template System

Create a reusable content template engine with these page types:

#### Template 1: Compliance Trigger Pages
```
Structure:
- H1: [State] [Regulation] Funding Guide for HOAs
- What is [regulation]? (plain English, 2-3 paragraphs)
- Key deadlines and requirements (table format)
- Financial impact on your association (cost ranges)
- Funding options comparison (loan vs special assessment vs reserves)
- How HOA Project Funding helps (CTA to pre-qual)
- FAQ section (5-8 questions, schema-marked)
- Related resources (internal links)
```

**Pages to generate (Priority 1 — publish in first 30 days):**

1. `florida-sirs-funding-guide` — Florida Structural Integrity Reserve Study financing
   - Tie to requirements effective Dec 31, 2024 and reserve restrictions
   - Target keywords: "SIRS funding", "structural integrity reserve study financing", "Florida condo reserve funding"

2. `florida-milestone-inspection-funding` — Florida milestone inspection financing
   - Tie to statutory milestone inspection obligations (§553.899)
   - Target keywords: "milestone inspection financing", "Florida building inspection funding"

3. `california-sb326-inspection-funding` — California SB 326 balcony/exterior inspection funding
   - Tie to SB 326 requirements and January 1, 2025 deadline
   - Target keywords: "SB 326 funding", "balcony inspection financing California", "exterior elevated elements"

4. `california-reserve-study-funding-gap` — California reserve study funding gap solutions
   - Tie to Civil Code §5550 three-year cadence
   - Target keywords: "reserve study funding gap", "California HOA underfunded reserves"

#### Template 2: Project-Type Financing Pages
```
Structure:
- H1: [Project Type] Financing for HOAs & Condos
- Why [project] costs spike (real data/ranges)
- How HOA loans work for [project type]
- What lenders evaluate (delinquencies, liquidity, assessment changes)
- Loan vs special assessment comparison for [project]
- Timeline: from board vote to funded project
- CTA to pre-qual
- Case study snippet (anonymized)
```

**Pages to generate (Priority 1):**

5. `hoa-roof-replacement-financing` — Roof replacement financing
6. `hoa-elevator-replacement-funding` — Elevator replacement funding
7. `condo-street-resurfacing-loan` — Street/parking resurfacing loans
8. `hoa-pool-renovation-financing` — Pool renovation financing
9. `condo-waterproofing-structural-repair-funding` — Waterproofing & structural repair

#### Template 3: Decision-Framing Pages
```
Structure:
- H1: [Decision Question] — What Your Board Needs to Know
- The real trade-offs (not sales copy — genuine education)
- Scenario comparison table (loan vs assessment vs hybrid)
- What lenders actually look at
- Board readiness checklist
- Member communication template snippet
- CTA to pre-qual
```

**Pages to generate (Priority 1):**

10. `hoa-loan-vs-special-assessment` — THE comparison page (highest intent keyword cluster)
    - Target: "HOA loan vs special assessment", "should HOA take out loan", "special assessment alternative"

11. `how-hoa-loans-work` — Educational deep-dive
    - Target: "how do HOA loans work", "HOA loan collateral", "do homeowners guarantee HOA loan"

12. `hoa-loan-readiness-checklist` — Board prep resource
    - Downloadable PDF checklist (lead magnet)
    - Target: "HOA loan requirements", "HOA loan documents needed"

