## Phase 4: Partner Distribution System (Days 14-30)

### Objective
Build outreach tooling and co-marketing assets for the three highest-leverage partner channels.

### Partner Channel 1: Property Management Companies (Highest Leverage)
**Why**: 9,000-10,000 management companies, each managing multiple associations. One partnership = many leads.

**Outreach sequence (5-touch, email-first):**
```
Touch 1 (Day 0): Value-first email
  Subject: "Quick question about [Company] associations needing capital projects"
  Body: Short, personal. Mention specific state compliance triggers.
  Attach: "Document Checklist for HOA Loan Readiness" PDF

Touch 2 (Day 3): Follow-up with case study
  Subject: "How a [XX]-unit HOA funded their roof in 45 days"
  Body: Anonymized case study. Emphasize manager's workflow stays simple.

Touch 3 (Day 7): Resource share
  Subject: "[State] compliance funding guide — for your board clients"
  Body: Link to relevant compliance trigger content page.
  Position as: "Something you can share with your boards"

Touch 4 (Day 14): Direct ask
  Subject: "15 min call — partnership for your associations?"
  Body: Propose partnership structure: we handle financing, you get smoother projects.

Touch 5 (Day 21): Break-up email
  Subject: "Closing the loop"
  Body: Final touch, leave door open.
```

**Co-marketing assets to create:**
- "Board Communication Kit" — Template letters/emails a manager can send to their board explaining loan vs assessment options
- "Financing FAQ for Board Meetings" — One-pager a manager can hand out at board meetings
- "Partner Portal" page concept — Where partners can submit leads and track status

### Partner Channel 2: Reserve Study Firms (Upstream Signal)
**Why**: They see funding gaps before anyone else. They deliver the report that reveals underfunding.

**Outreach approach:**
- Lead with California (Civil Code §5550 cadence creates constant pipeline)
- Offer: "When your study reveals a funding gap, give the board our checklist alongside your report"
- Co-brand: "[Reserve Study Firm] + HOA Project Funding — From Study to Solution"
- Create a one-page "Funding Gap? Here's What to Do Next" insert they can include with their reports

### Partner Channel 3: Construction Vendors (Roofing, Structural, Waterproofing, Paving)
**Why**: Vendors lose projects when boards can't fund them. We solve that.

**Outreach approach:**
- Lead with: "Stop losing projects to 'we can't afford it' — we pre-qualify HOAs for financing"
- Offer: "Send us the board's info, we pre-qualify them, you close your project"
- Co-brand: "[Vendor] + HOA Project Funding — Financing Available" badge for their proposals
- Create a vendor-specific referral page and tracking code

### Technical Implementation

```
/partner-system/
├── outreach/
│   ├── sequences/
│   │   ├── management-company-5touch.md    # Email copy for all 5 touches
│   │   ├── reserve-study-firm-3touch.md    # Email copy
│   │   └── vendor-contractor-3touch.md     # Email copy
│   ├── templates/
│   │   ├── board-communication-kit.docx    # Co-marketing asset
│   │   ├── financing-faq-one-pager.pdf     # Board meeting handout
│   │   ├── funding-gap-insert.pdf          # For reserve study firms
│   │   └── vendor-financing-badge.svg      # "Financing Available" badge
