## Phase 5: Nurture & Follow-Up System (Days 21-35)

### Objective
Build compliant email/SMS sequences that keep non-ready leads warm and convert them when timing is right.

### Email Nurture Sequences

#### Sequence 1: Post Pre-Qual Nurture (C/D-tier leads)
```
Email 1 (Day 0): "Your HOA Loan Readiness Report"
  — Personalized based on their pre-qual answers
  — "Here's what lenders will look for from your association"
  — Link to readiness checklist

Email 2 (Day 7): "HOA Loan vs Special Assessment — What Your Board Should Know"
  — Link to decision-framing content
  — Position as education, not sales

Email 3 (Day 14): "What Lenders Actually Evaluate (And How to Prepare)"
  — Delinquencies, liquidity, assessment history
  — Practical tips to improve lender attractiveness

Email 4 (Day 28): "How to Present Financing Options at Your Board Meeting"
  — Board communication template
  — Meeting agenda snippet
  — "Ready to get options? Start your pre-qualification"

Email 5 (Day 45): "Quick Check-In: Has Your Project Timeline Changed?"
  — Simple re-engagement
  — Link back to pre-qual form
```

#### Sequence 2: Post Application Follow-Up (awaiting docs)
```
Email 1 (Day 0): "We've received your pre-qualification — here's what's next"
  — Specific document checklist (state-adjusted)
  — Upload link

Email 2 (Day 3): "Quick tip: gathering your documents faster"
  — Specific tips for getting reserve study, financials, minutes
  — "Most associations complete this in 5-7 days"

Email 3 (Day 7): "Checking in — need help with documents?"
  — Offer phone support
  — Common sticking points and solutions
```

#### Sequence 3: Post Funded — Referral & Testimonial
```
Email 1 (Day 30 post-close): "How is your [project type] going?"
  — Check-in, relationship maintenance

Email 2 (Day 45 post-close): "Would you share your experience?"
  — Testimonial request (short form)
  — Google review request

Email 3 (Day 60 post-close): "Know another board that needs funding?"
  — Referral program introduction
  — "Share with your management company"
```

### Compliance Requirements (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

**CAN-SPAM (email):**
- Every email must include: physical mailing address, clear unsubscribe mechanism, honest subject lines
- Unsubscribe requests honored within 10 business days
- No purchased email lists — all contacts must have given consent through our forms

**TCPA (SMS/text):**
- Explicit written consent required before any text messages
- Consent language must be clear: "By providing your phone number, you agree to receive text messages from HOA Project Funding about your loan inquiry. Reply STOP to unsubscribe. Msg & data rates may apply."
- Maintain opt-out records
- No texts before 8am or after 9pm in recipient's time zone

