│   ├── unsubscribe-handler.ts       # Immediate unsubscribe processing
│   ├── sms-opt-in-tracker.ts        # TCPA consent records
│   └── sending-hours.ts             # Timezone-aware sending windows
└── analytics/
    ├── sequence-metrics.ts          # Open rates, click rates, conversions per sequence
    └── attribution.ts               # Which sequence/email drove the conversion?
```

---

## Phase 6: Analytics & Feedback Loops (Days 28-42)

### Objective
Instrument everything so every dollar spent and every lead generated produces measurable intelligence.

### Analytics Architecture

**Layer 1: Traffic Analytics (GA4)**
- Page-level tracking for all content pages
- Event tracking: form starts, pre-qual completions, full application submissions, document uploads
- UTM parameter tracking for all inbound sources
- Custom dimensions: state, project type, lead source, partner attribution

**Layer 2: Pipeline Analytics (HubSpot + Custom)**
- Cost per lead by source (organic, paid, partner, outbound)
- Cost per QUALIFIED lead (pre-qual pass rate × CPL)
- Conversion rate by pipeline stage
- Average time in each pipeline stage
- Close rate by project type, state, lead source
- Average loan size by segment
- Revenue per closed deal

**Layer 3: Content Performance**
- Organic rankings for target keywords (track weekly)
- Content → lead attribution (which page generated the lead?)
- Content engagement: time on page, scroll depth, CTA click rate
- Content gap analysis: what are people searching that we don't have pages for?

**Layer 4: Partner Performance**
- Leads per partner
- Conversion rate per partner
- Revenue attribution per partner channel
- Partner engagement: are they actively referring?

### Feedback Loop Automations

```
Every Closed Won deal triggers:
→ Add to "Case Study Queue" (anonymized data auto-extracted)
→ Calculate: cost-per-unit for this project type + state
→ Update internal benchmarks
→ Generate "What it cost" data snippet for content pages
→ Tag content page that originated the lead (attribution loop)

Every Closed Lost deal triggers:
→ Categorize loss reason
→ IF reason is "inadequate reserves" → Generate content: "How to Build Reserves Before Borrowing"
→ IF reason is "board vote failed" → Generate content: "How to Present Financing at Board Meetings"
→ IF reason is "high delinquency" → Generate content: "Reducing Delinquencies to Qualify for Loans"
→ Queue rejected lead for re-engagement when conditions change

Monthly automated report:
→ Top performing content pages (by lead generation)
→ Pipeline health (deals by stage, velocity, conversion rates)
→ Partner scoreboard
→ Keyword ranking changes
→ Recommended content topics (from search console + loss reasons)
```

### Technical Implementation

```
/analytics/
├── tracking/
│   ├── ga4-config.ts               # GA4 setup, custom events, dimensions
│   ├── event-definitions.ts        # Standardized event taxonomy
│   └── utm-handler.ts              # UTM parameter capture and storage
├── dashboards/
│   ├── pipeline-dashboard.tsx       # Real-time pipeline visualization
│   ├── content-performance.tsx      # Content → lead attribution
│   ├── partner-scoreboard.tsx       # Partner performance tracking
│   └── roi-calculator.tsx           # CPL, conversion, revenue metrics
├── reports/
│   ├── monthly-report-generator.ts  # Auto-generate monthly report
│   └── report-template.md           # Monthly report template
└── feedback-loops/
    ├── case-study-generator.ts      # Auto-draft from closed-won data
    ├── content-gap-analyzer.ts      # Identify missing content from search data
    └── loss-reason-content-mapper.ts # Map loss reasons → content topics
```

---

## Phase 7: OpenClaw Agent Integration (Days 35-56)

### Objective
Connect the marketing machine to OpenClaw browser automation agents for tasks that are repetitive, data-heavy, or time-sensitive.

### Agent Tasks to Automate

#### Agent 1: Competitor & Market Monitor
```
Schedule: Weekly
Actions:
- Scan competitor sites (HOA Loan Services, bank HOA lending pages) for new content/offers
- Check Google for ranking changes on target keywords
- Monitor CAI/FCAR for new publications or data
- Monitor state legislature sites for new HOA-related legislation (FL, CA, TX)
- Compile weekly intelligence brief
Output: Markdown report → ClawOps Console → Team notification
```

#### Agent 2: Partner Prospect Research
```
Schedule: On-demand + weekly batch
Actions:
- Search for property management companies in target states
- Extract: company name, website, contact info, portfolio size (if available)
- Search for reserve study firms in California
- Search for roofing/structural contractors in FL and CA
- Enrich with LinkedIn profiles where available
- Score prospects by portfolio size and location
Output: CSV → CRM import ready
```

#### Agent 3: Content Performance Tracker
```
Schedule: Daily
Actions:
- Check Google Search Console API for ranking data
- Track positions for all target keywords
- Identify pages gaining/losing traffic
- Check for new "People Also Ask" questions in target keyword clusters
- Flag content opportunities
Output: Dashboard update + weekly summary
```

#### Agent 4: Lead Enrichment
```
Trigger: New pre-qual submission
Actions:
- Look up the association (if identifiable) for public records
- Check state databases for any compliance filings
- Cross-reference with Fannie Mae/Freddie Mac condo project eligibility (if available)
- Enrich CRM record with findings
Output: Enriched CRM record + enrichment notes
```

#### Agent 5: Compliance Deadline Monitor
```
Schedule: Monthly
Actions:
- Monitor Florida DBPR for SIRS/milestone inspection updates
- Monitor California DRE for reserve study and SB 326 enforcement updates
- Check for new county-level HOA regulations in target markets
- Identify associations approaching known deadlines
Output: Compliance alert report → Priority outreach list
```

### Technical Implementation

```
/openclaw-agents/
├── agents/
│   ├── competitor-monitor/
│   │   ├── agent-config.yaml        # OpenClaw agent definition
│   │   ├── targets.json             # Sites/keywords to monitor
│   │   └── report-template.md       # Weekly report format
│   ├── partner-research/
│   │   ├── agent-config.yaml
│   │   ├── search-queries.json      # Search patterns by partner type
│   │   └── enrichment-rules.json    # What data to extract
│   ├── content-tracker/
│   │   ├── agent-config.yaml
│   │   ├── keyword-list.json        # All target keywords
│   │   └── alert-thresholds.json    # When to flag changes
│   ├── lead-enrichment/
│   │   ├── agent-config.yaml
│   │   ├── lookup-sources.json      # Public databases to check
│   │   └── enrichment-schema.json   # Standardized output format
│   └── compliance-monitor/
│       ├── agent-config.yaml
│       ├── regulatory-sources.json  # State agency sites to monitor
│       └── deadline-tracker.json    # Known upcoming deadlines
├── scheduling/
│   ├── cron-config.yaml             # Agent run schedules
│   └── trigger-config.yaml          # Event-driven agent triggers
└── outputs/
    ├── reports/                      # Agent output reports
    └── data/                         # Structured data exports
```

---

## Phase 8: Paid Acquisition (Days 42-60, budget-permitting)

### Objective
Only after organic and partner channels are producing data, layer in small-budget Google Ads on proven high-intent keywords.

### Budget: Start at $500-$1,000/month MAX

**At industry benchmarks ($84-$100 CPL), this buys 5-12 leads per month.** The goal isn't volume — it's validation and learning.

### Campaign Structure

```
Campaign 1: Compliance Triggers (Highest Intent)
  Ad Group: Florida SIRS
    Keywords: "SIRS funding", "structural integrity reserve study financing", "Florida condo reserve loan"
  Ad Group: Florida Milestone
    Keywords: "milestone inspection financing", "Florida building inspection loan"
  Ad Group: California SB 326
    Keywords: "SB 326 funding", "balcony inspection financing"

Campaign 2: Decision Intent
  Ad Group: Loan vs Assessment
    Keywords: "HOA loan vs special assessment", "special assessment alternative HOA"
  Ad Group: Project Financing
    Keywords: "HOA roof replacement loan", "condo elevator financing"

Campaign 3: Direct Intent (Exact/Phrase Match Only)
  Ad Group: Core
    Keywords: "HOA loan", "HOA financing", "condo association loan"
```

### Landing Pages (one per ad group, minimum)
Each landing page must:
- Match the ad's keyword intent precisely
- Include the trust stack elements from Phase 2
- Lead to the pre-qual form (not full application)
- Have GA4 conversion tracking
- Be mobile-optimized (60%+ of HOA board members search on mobile)
- Load in <3 seconds

### Negative Keywords (prevent waste)
```
-job -jobs -salary -career -resume
-template -free -sample (careful — some are OK)
-"property management" (unless targeting that segment)
-DIY -"how to" (unless on educational pages)
```

### Success Metrics
- Target CPL: <$100 (at or below industry benchmark)
- Target pre-qual completion rate: >15%
- Target qualified rate: >40% of pre-qual completions
- Break-even: CPL / close-rate ≤ revenue-per-close

---

## Phase 9: SaaS Foundation (Days 56-90, parallel track)

### Objective
Begin capturing the data and building the interfaces that will become the SaaS product. This is NOT a separate build — it's capturing what the marketing machine already produces.

### Data Capture (Start Now — Even Before SaaS)

Every interaction in the marketing machine should feed the future SaaS:

```
Data to capture from Day 1:
- Association profiles (state, units, age, occupancy, assessments, delinquency)
- Project profiles (type, scope, cost, timeline, urgency driver)
- Lender response data (offers received, rates/terms ranges, turnaround time)
- Outcome data (close/no-close, reasons, final terms)
- Document metadata (reserve study date, inspection dates, board vote dates)
- Compliance status (which regulations apply, deadline proximity)
```

### SaaS MVP Features (Build When Ready)

1. **HOA Funding Readiness Score** — Auto-generated assessment of how lender-ready an association is
2. **Project Funding Workspace** — Upload docs once, request bids for multiple projects
3. **Compliance Calendar** — State-specific deadlines and requirements dashboard
4. **Owner Communication Generator** — Template letters, FAQs, meeting agendas for board-to-owner communication about financing decisions
5. **Lender Portal** — Standardized bid request interface for participating lenders

### Distribution via Existing Ecosystems
Target integrations (start with "export lender-ready packet" — minimal integration overhead):
- TownSq (board/homeowner/manager workflows)
- Vantaca (community association management)
- CINC Systems (association management, already has bank partners)
- Enumerate (community association management)

---

## Execution Summary & Priority Order

```
WEEK 1-2 (Foundation):
├── Set up HubSpot Free CRM with custom properties and pipeline stages
├── Build pre-qual scoring algorithm and form
├── Create first 6 SEO content pages (compliance triggers + decision pages)
├── Set up GA4 with custom events
└── Draft consent language (CAN-SPAM + TCPA compliant)

WEEK 2-3 (Pipeline):
├── Build full application form (Stage 2)
├── Create lender intake packet generator (PDF)
├── Set up n8n/Make workflows (new lead processing, document collection)
├── Build email templates (pre-qual pass, nurture, docs request)
└── Launch first nurture sequence

WEEK 3-4 (Distribution):
├── Create partner outreach sequences (management companies first)
├── Build co-marketing assets (Board Communication Kit, checklists)
├── Publish remaining SEO pages (project types)
├── Begin outreach: 50-100 management companies
└── Begin outreach: 20 reserve study firms (CA)

WEEK 4-6 (Scale & Automate):
├── Configure OpenClaw agents (competitor monitor, partner research)
├── Build analytics dashboards
├── Launch second nurture sequence (post-funded referral)
├── Begin outreach: 20 contractors (roofing/structural)
└── Set up feedback loop automations (case study generator, content gap analyzer)

WEEK 6-8 (Optimize & Paid):
├── Analyze first 30 days of data
├── Optimize content based on Search Console data
├── Launch Google Ads test ($500-$1,000 budget)
├── Create ad-specific landing pages
└── Refine scoring algorithm based on real conversion data

WEEK 8-12 (SaaS Foundation & Scale):
├── Begin SaaS data capture layer
├── Expand state-specific content libraries (TX, IL, NY, etc.)
├── Scale partner outreach based on what's working
├── Build partner portal (lead submission + tracking)
└── Evaluate SaaS MVP features based on accumulated data
```

